i>â¢bahya = external</li>\r\n	<li>â¢abhyantara = internal</li>\r\n	<li>â¢stambha = holding, restraint, suspension, retention, cessation</li>\r\n	<li>â¢vrittih = movements, fluctuations</li>\r\n	<li>â¢desha = place, spot, space, location</li>\r\n	<li>â¢kala = time, period, duration</li>\r\n	<li>â¢sankhyabhih = by these three, number, count of</li>\r\n	<li>â¢paridrishtah = regulated by, observed by</li>\r\n	<li>â¢dirgha = made long, prolonged, slow</li>\r\n	<li>â¢sukshmah = and subtle, fine</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nà¤¬à¤¾à¤¹à¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤­à¥à¤¯à¤¨à¥à¤¤à¤°à¤µà¤¿à¤·à¤¯à¤¾à¤à¥à¤·à¥à¤ªà¥ à¤à¤¤à¥à¤°à¥à¤¥à¤à¥¥à¥«à¥§à¥¥\r\n\r\n<b>PYS 2.51: BÄhya abhyantara viÅaya aká¹£epi chaturthaá¸¥Â </b>\r\n\r\n<i>beyond this is the froth method of breathing, which surpasses the internal and external realms of breathÂ </i>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>â¢bahya = external</li>\r\n	<li>â¢abhyantara = internal</li>\r\n	<li>â¢vishaya = region, spheres, realms, fields</li>\r\n	<li>â¢akshepi = going beyond, surpassing, setting aside</li>\r\n	<li>â¢chaturthah = the fourth</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nà¤¤à¤¤à¤ à¤à¥à¤·à¥à¤¯à¤¤à¥ à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤à¤¾à¤¶à¤¾à¤µà¤°à¤£à¤®à¥à¥¥à¥«à¥¨à¥¥\r\n\r\n<b>PYS 2.52: Tataá¸¥ kÅÄ«yate prakaÅa ÄvaranamÂ </b>\r\n\r\n<i>than the veil covering the illumination vanishesÂ </i>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>â¢tatah = then, thereby, thence, from that</li>\r\n	<li>â¢kshiyate = is destroyed, thinned, diminishes, vanishes</li>\r\n	<li>â¢prakasha = light, illumination</li>\r\n	<li>â¢avaranam = veil, covering<i>\r\n</i></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPranayama is the highest discipline on the yogic path. The most powerful tool of <b><i>practice</i></b> (Abhyasa) to allow the next four stages to happen through letting go or <b><i>renunciation</i></b> (Vairagya).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe initiation of this practice is done by experienced teacher to avoid damage to the nervous system which can be caused by incorrect and inappropriate use of the techniques.', 'PrÄnÄyÄma', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '56-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-10 20:58:33', '2013-11-10 20:58:33', '', 56, 'http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/?p=57', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(58, 1, '2013-11-10 21:00:06', '2013-11-10 21:00:06', '<i>DhÄranÄ</i> (à¤§à¤¾à¤°à¤£à¤¾) is another involutionary stage of yoga. Literally it means concentration. In this state the mind is intensely focussed in one-pointed concentration.\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-43" alt="Ashtanga Yoga" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/shapeimage_42.png" width="883" height="512" /></p>\r\nà¤§à¤¾à¤°à¤£à¤¾à¤¸à¥ à¤ à¤¯à¥à¤à¥à¤¯à¤¤à¤¾ à¤®à¤¨à¤¸à¤à¥¥à¥«à¥©à¥¥\r\n\r\n<b>PYS 2.53: DhÄranÄsu Äa YogyatÄ ManasahÂ </b>\r\n\r\n<i>the fourth Pranayama prepares the mind for concentration</i>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>â¢dharanasu = for concentration, for dharana</li>\r\n	<li>â¢cha = and</li>\r\n	<li>â¢yogyata = fitness, preparedness, qualification, capability</li>\r\n	<li>â¢manasah = mind</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nà¤¦à¥à¤¶à¤¬à¤¨à¥à¤§à¤¶à¥à¤à¤¿à¤¤à¥à¤¤à¤¸à¥à¤¯ à¤§à¤¾à¤°à¤£à¤¾à¥¥à¥§à¥¥\r\n\r\n<b>PYS 3.1: DeÅah bandhah cittasya dhÄranÄÂ </b>\r\n\r\n<i>attention fixed upon one point is DhÄranÄ; concentration Â </i>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>â¢deshah = place, object, point, spot</li>\r\n	<li>â¢bandhah = binding to, holding, fixing, uniting</li>\r\n	<li>â¢chittasya = of the mind, consciousness</li>\r\n	<li>â¢dharana = concentration, focusing, directing attention</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;', 'DhÄranÄ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'dharana', '', '', '2013-12-02 16:46:17', '2013-12-02 16:46:17', '', 41, 'http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/?page_id=58', 6, 'page', '', 0),
